msgid "Trainer Checklists"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:18
msgid "Running an Instructor Training Event (General)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:20
msgid "Four weeks before the event"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:21
msgid "Contact your co-Trainer(s) and decide who will teach what."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:22
msgid ""
"Create an event Etherpad (using the Etherpad template) or Google Doc (using "
"the Google Doc template) and a workshop website (using the training "
"template).  Note the Google Doc is not currently maintained and may not be "
"in sync with lesson materials."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:23
msgid ""
"Send Etherpad/Google Doc and website links to training@carpentries.org."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:25
msgid "One week before the event"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:26
msgid "Plan logistics with co-Trainer(s)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:27
msgid ""
"Review (or set aside time closer to the event to review) the pre-assessment "
"survey results for your workshop"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:28
msgid "If teaching remotely:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:29
#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:81
msgid "Get acquanted with using Zoom for videoconferencing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:30
msgid ""
"Test videoconferencing set up with co-Trainer(s) using login credentials "
"provided."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:31
msgid ""
"Decide with co-Trainer(s) whether all Trainers should be present for the "
"full event or if you will log on during your scheduled teaching times only."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:32
msgid ""
"Make a copy of the Virtual Minute Cards template and personalize for your "
"event."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:33
msgid "If teaching in person:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:34
msgid ""
"Confirm with your host that breakout rooms are available or make an "
"alternate plan"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:35
msgid ""
"Create a plan for printing handouts & determine who will bring sticky notes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:36
msgid ""
"Make sure you're prepared for the audiovisual setup in your room with the "
"correct dongles/connectors etc."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:37
msgid ""
"Check on availability/timing of coffee, lunch, or any other details that "
"matter to you"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:39
msgid "During the event"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:40
msgid "Take attendance."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:41
msgid ""
"Remind member trainees to fill out application (Open Training applicants "
"have already done this)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:42
msgid ""
"Remind trainees to sign up for demo, discussion (links in checkout "
"checklist)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:43
msgid ""
"Monitor the Etherpad / Google Doc for questions and responses to exercises."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:44
msgid ""
"If teaching remotely: Turn off video during long exercises and coffee breaks"
" and disconnect during lunch."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:46
msgid "Immediately after the event"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:47
msgid ""
"Send a list of those who completed the training to checkout@carpentries."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:48
msgid ""
"Send an email to trainees thanking them for participating and linking to "
"checkout checklist using this template"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:49
msgid ""
"Review survey results and prepare to discuss at upcoming Trainers discussion"
" meeting."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:50
msgid "File any relevant issues or PRs to the instructor training repo."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:52
msgid "Long-term after the event"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:53
msgid "Join a Trainer meeting to discuss how your event went."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:55
msgid "Differences Between In-person and Online Training Events"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:57
msgid "In-person trainings"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:58
msgid "When watching videos, project them to the whole group."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:59
#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:64
msgid "Assign (or let participants select) physical breakout groups."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:60
msgid ""
"Use physical sticky notes to get minute card feedback at lunch breaks and "
"end of each day."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:62
msgid "Online trainings (a few small groups)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:63
msgid ""
"When watching videos, have one Trainer do a screenshare with their audio on "
"or have one person in each group play the video for the participants at "
"their site."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:65
#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:71
msgid ""
"Use the virtual minute card form to get feedback at lunch breaks and end of "
"each day."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:66
msgid ""
"Have participants do all small-group exercises with participants at same "
"site."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:68
msgid "Online trainings (completely distributed)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:69
msgid "When watching videos, have all participants watch separately."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:70
msgid ""
"Assign breakout groups randomly to breakout rooms in Zoom. Be sure to remove"
" Trainers and helpers when assigning groups."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:72
msgid ""
"Have participants screen share with their breakout room during the live "
"coding exercises."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:73
msgid ""
"For exercise to set up a workshop website, put participants in breakout "
"rooms and have one person screen share while the others help guide them "
"verbally."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:75
msgid "Running a Teaching Demonstration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:77
msgid ""
"If you would like to watch an example teaching demo, there is a recording of"
" one here."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:79
msgid "Before the demo"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:80
msgid "Sign up to lead demos."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:82
msgid ""
"For each trainee, pick a suitable starting point in the lesson that they "
"have chosen. Suggested lessons are available in the Instructor Training "
"Curriculum (under Extras). Do not have them start in the middle of an "
"episode. Note that some lessons (e.g., the Software Carpentry R lesson using"
" inflammation data) have supplementary episodes. Do not pick from those."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:84
msgid "During the Demo"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:85
msgid "Go to the Zoom room. The link is in the Etherpad."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:86
msgid ""
"Once everyone is in the call (audio and video working), remind them of the "
"Code of Conduct, explain the procedure for the demo session, and remind them"
" that trainees have to be able to teach from any episode from their chosen "
"lesson. Ask whether anyone has only prepared for 5 minutes from one episode "
"instead of the entire lesson, and if so, suggest strongly they reschedule. "
"It can help to remind them that this is not a high stakes test but a "
"friendly opportunity for feedback."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:87
msgid ""
"Ask those not presenting to mute their microphone, and ask them to give "
"feedback using the same positive-vs-negative and content-vs-presentation "
"rubric used in training. For a full session (5 trainees), they should add "
"feedback to the etherpad. If you have fewer people, you may choose to have "
"them jot down comments and deliver them verbally as time allows."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:88
msgid ""
"Give the assignment to the first trainee, then give them a bit of time to "
"set up the demo (they may have to import some packages, load some data, move"
" to a certain folder etc)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:89
msgid ""
"Ask them to share their screen using the “Share Screen” lower menu in Zoom."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:90
msgid "Once they are ready, give them a 3-2-1 countdown to start."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:91
msgid ""
"Use a countdown timer which makes a noise once their 5 minutes are up (e.g.,"
" your phone), or just say “bong” really loudly at the end of their time."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:92
msgid ""
"After the five minute timer, allow them to finish their sentence and tell "
"them time’s up."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:93
msgid "Use a rubric to help you take notes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:94
msgid ""
"After the trainee is finished, first ask how they themselves thought it "
"went. If you have time, other trainees can give verbal feedback, or you can "
"summarize what is in the etherpad. Then, give focused, constructive feedback"
" based on your notes and the comments of others. You might choose one or two"
" things to particularly emphasize to help focus trainees' efforts as they "
"proceed to teach a workshop. It is also sometimes necessary to take time to "
"(gently) disagree with feedback from another trainee."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:95
msgid ""
"Do NOT tell a trainee whether they passed immediately after their demo."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:96
msgid "Repeat for the other trainees."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:97
msgid "At the end of the season, ask for general questions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:98
msgid ""
"If all of your trainees passed, you can tell the group at the end of the "
"demo session. If anyone did not pass, tell everyone you will send them each "
"an email to let them know if they passed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:100
msgid "During the Demo (Troubleshooting)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:101
msgid "Refer to the Zoom guide to help troubleshoot connection issues."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:102
msgid ""
"If a trainee is teaching a Python lesson and their Jupyter notebook doesn't "
"start, direct them to http://jupyter.org/try."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:104
msgid "After the Demo"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:105
msgid ""
"Email checkout@carpentries.org with names, pass/fail, and SWC/DC/LC for each"
" of your trainees."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:106
msgid "Clear Etherpad of data from your session."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:107
msgid ""
"Send each trainee an email letting them know they passed or did not pass the"
" teaching demo. If needed, let them know the reason they did not pass and "
"asking them to retry."
msgstr ""

